Narrow-angle glaucoma presenting as acute, painless visual impairment.
 A 42-year-old woman presented with the acute onset of bilateral blurred vision that occurred immediately after bending over.
 She denied pain or any other associated symptoms.
 Markedly increased intraocular pressure readings were found.
 Treatment for acute narrow-angle glaucoma was initiated, and normal vision returned.
 This case represents an atypical presentation of acute narrow-angle glaucoma, a true ophthalmological emergency.
 The pathophysiology and treatment options of this disease process are summarized.
